Suite 110 Nashville, TN 37203 615/255-6270.615/255-6271 (fax), ..jrolwing@tnbio.org TENNESSEE BIDTECHNDLDGY ASSOCIATION AGREEMENT THE TENNESSEE BOARD OF REGENTS (INVESTOR) and the TENESSEE BIOTECHNOLOGY ASSOCIATION (TBA) agree that the State of Tennessee should have an exhibit at the Biotechnology Industry Organization’s BI02008 trade show to be held in San Diego, CA during the period June 17-20, 2008. The parties further agree that the cost of this exhibit will be funded by several organizations. INVESTOR agrees to pay $5,000 towards the cost of sponsoring this Tennessee exhibit at BI02008, to name the below person as a representative who will participate in decision making and to receive notices and reports, and to send staff to San Diego, CA to assist in staffing the exhibit during the operating hours. We anticipate the exhibit to be open approximately twenty-three hours over the three days of this event. Volunteers from other non-investors may be available to fill this need at their expense. INVESTOR also agrees that it is their responsibility to take full advantage of this investment by being informed of all of the opportunities made available at this event by the Biotechnology Industry Organization Named INVESTOR representative and contact information: Dr. p.n.da Myrick Short, Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs TBA agrees to properly account for this investment, to give INVESTOR periodic progress reports, to give a minimum of ten days notice of any telephone conference calls or meetings, to give the INVESTOR representative a final accounting of the total investment, and to return a pro rata share of any unspent funds.
